column2: Lake very low. Good weather but dry. Lake appears to be in bloom.
Plenty of rain and lake appears to be in good shape.
Plenty of rain and water is full of lake "bloom".
Water and lake are in good shape and there is plenty of rain.
Lake is in good shape- weeds coming on strong and cloud use rain.
Need rain and weeds are in abundance.
Lake is clearing up and weeds are going down.
Lake in good shape. Weeds starting to show.
Water clear. Lake getting very weedy. Still in good shape.
Water clear. Lake weedy- but in good shape.
Water murky. Weeds down. Algae on water.
Weeds are up.  Lake condition looks good.  Water warm enough to swim.
Water in good condition - plenty of rain.
Weeds in abundance.  Water low.  Water condition acceptable.
Weeds still high.  Water low.  Algae showing up.  Need rain to flush lake.
Weeds going down - water low.  Algae getting worse.  Really need rain.
Weeds going down - water murky.  No algae.  Rain helping.
Weeds are up - water is high.
McCabes are in the office on 8/30 to get info. put into the data base
Water condition is good - weeds are thick.  Fishing is poor.
Wawter condition is good- water high.  Ample weeds.
Water condition good - water high - weed condition serious.
Lake water very clear. Partly sunny- light breeze; Weed and wild rice influx serious.  Algae increasing.
Lake loaded with algae - weeds are down.  Fishing poor all season.
Day was cold and gray. Lake was slightly choppy from the wind.
water is low-weeds are showing up- algae starting
Lake clear except for duckweed on surface. partly Sunny with light wind.
water high- algae showing on top- planety of rain-fishing poor
warm-sunny and windy. Lake appears to be very clear.
Day was very windy and cloudy all day. Temp about 90 degrees.Water was choppy but clear
water about normal- windy- lake riled- weeds showing on surface
Two storm days preceded this day. Water appeared darker
water a little low- need rain- weeds getting thick
water a little low- windy- water clear- plenty of weeds- no fish
calm- sunny day. There has been little rain for the last couple of weeks but frequent strong winds.
water a little low- windy- water riled up- need rain- again pleanty of weeds
Day warm and sunny. Water clear and calm.
water low- need rain- weeds starting to recede- wild rice spreading
water low- wild rice showing around lake- water ok
Calm + sunny.  Water very green.  Algae bloom.  Air temp is 55 .
water low- need rain- weeds receding- fishing poor
water a little low- weeds receding- fish poor
water a little low- weeds continue to recede- fishing poor- some rain
water low- need rain- weeds down- fishing poor- water not bad
water level ok- weeds down- fishing poor
These readings were taken following a rainfall of 1.5 inches on the previous day. The lake has a very heavy pea-green algae bloom.
Lake is frozen over. Slushy on top. Ice thickness about 12 inches.
Water very clear- calm. Some fishing and boating activity.
Sunny and breezy day. Lake slightly greener than in May but still clear. Secchi readings have been 11 the past couple of weeks
water very clear- weeds are coming up
water clear- lake weedy- need rain
Sunny- calm.   The lake color was green.
Sunny and a slight breeze. Water appears very green from certain view points
The lake was very calm. Surface water had lots of floating stuff- insects- dead weeds etc. near the shore.
water getting murky- weedy- no rain
water somewhat murky- 1" rain- still weedy
Water murky- 2" rain- weeds getting lower
Sunny day-no clouds- slight breeze. Water very green-algae bloom
water very murky- algae thick- weeds going down- need rain
water very poor condition- algae thick. abundance of weed waste
water condition poor- algae thick- weeds going down
algae still abundant- need rain- wild rice in poor condition
still full of algae-  weeds down- last test of season
Nice day...Breezy and sunny..water slightly choppy. Algae bloom
Lake water has algae bloom. Green particles visible. Also globs of green material. Water is in very bad condition.
Cloudy- breezy-lake has algae bloom-bottom of lake not readily visible along the shore. Temp about 55 F
Bright sunny day- windy and cold
Partly sunny- very windy- lake water is murky.
lAKE VERY MURKY- LARGE "TAR BALLS"- GOBS OF BLACK SLIME ARE PRESENT EVERYWHERE ON THE SURFACE. lAKE VERY MURKY- LARGE "TAR BALLS"- GOBS OF BLACK SLIME ARE PRESENT EVERYWHERE ON THE SURFACE.
Calm-clear.  Lake is beautiful except for a very few small- 2 inch diameter- blobs of aphanocapsa- black algae.
water clear and low   abundance of weeds
algae starting to show   water low
lake level very low- algae- plenty of weeds
Lake low - algae  weeds  poor appearance
Lake in poor condition- weeds - algae - very low
water in poor shape- weeds going down- algae   need rain
water starting to clear  need rain
Lake is very calm.  Pine pollen is on the surface of the lake- making it look green.  Water clarity is very good.

There is some algae in the water- as the lake has a greenish color.  Neighbor reported secchi disc readings of 8'.  Also- we saw some small "globs" of black algae- which we have been told are aphanacapsa( ).  The water temperature has dropped about 7 degrees since last week.
The lake is looking a little green with algae at this time.  Plant growth seems to be slightly less now- as cool temperatures are holding down the water temperature.
lake has turned- getting more clarity
clear- breezy- 1.5" rain last two weeks
cloudy- light wind- 3.5" rain last two weeks
clear day- light wind- 2.25 inch rain last two weeks
clear day- lots of boat traffic
